<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Buildkit on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/buildkit/</link><description>Recent content in Buildkit on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/buildkit/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] Docker Build Cache Error — build cache error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/docker/docker-build-cache/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/docker/docker-build-cache/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;A Docker build cache error occurs when the build cache is corrupted or incompatible. This can cause builds to fail or produce unexpected results.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Corrupted build cache from an interrupted build&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cache mount points not available during build&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BuildKit cache backend issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Insufficient disk space for cache storage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cross-platform build cache incompatibility&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="prune-build-cache"&gt;Prune Build Cache&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;docker builder prune
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="clear-all-build-cache"&gt;Clear All Build Cache&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;docker builder prune -a
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="disable-build-cache"&gt;Disable Build Cache&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;docker build --no-cache -t my-image .
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="check-buildkit-status"&gt;Check BuildKit Status&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;DOCKER_BUILDKIT&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; docker build -t my-image .
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="set-cache-exportimport"&gt;Set Cache Export/Import&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;docker build --cache-from type&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;registry,ref&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;my-image:latest -t my-image .
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Example 1: Clear and rebuild&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;docker builder prune -a
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;docker build -t my-image .
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Example 2: Build without cache&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;docker build --no-cache -t my-image .
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Example 3: Use BuildKit for better caching&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;DOCKER_BUILDKIT&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; docker build --progress&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;plain -t my-image .
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/docker/docker-image-not-found/"&gt;Docker Image Not Found&lt;/a&gt; — image not found in registry&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/docker/docker-pull-timeout/"&gt;Docker Pull Timeout&lt;/a&gt; — Docker pull timeout&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Docker Build Cache Error — Fix BuildKit Cache Failures</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/linux-docker-build-cache/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/linux-docker-build-cache/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="docker-build-cache-error--fix-buildkit-cache-failures"&gt;Docker Build Cache Error — Fix BuildKit Cache Failures&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A Docker build cache error occurs when &lt;code&gt;docker build&lt;/code&gt; fails due to a corrupted or inaccessible build cache. The error reads:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;error: failed to solve: error getting build cache: reference not found&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Or:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;WARNING: buildx: cache export error: No such image&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Docker builds images in layers. Each Dockerfile instruction creates a new layer, and Docker caches these layers to speed up subsequent builds. When the cache becomes corrupted, references are lost, or the cache export/import fails, the build fails. BuildKit (the default builder in Docker 23+) uses a more sophisticated cache backend that can encounter these issues.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Docker BuildKit — failed to solve</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/docker/docker-buildkit/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/docker/docker-buildkit/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="docker-buildkit--failed-to-solve"&gt;Docker BuildKit — failed to solve&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;BuildKit errors occur when the modern Docker build engine cannot complete the build. BuildKit provides faster builds with caching but has stricter requirements on Dockerfile syntax and build context.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build context is too large or contains forbidden paths&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cache mount issues with package managers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Network failure during build step requiring remote resources&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Invalid Dockerfile syntax not caught by legacy builder&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="enable-buildkit"&gt;Enable BuildKit&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Set environment variable&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;export DOCKER_BUILDKIT&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Or in daemon.json&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# { &amp;#34;features&amp;#34;: { &amp;#34;buildkit&amp;#34;: true } }&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="add-dockerignore"&gt;Add .dockerignore&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-text" data-lang="text"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;# .dockerignore
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;node_modules
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;.git
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;*.md
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;.env
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;docker-compose*.yml
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="check-build-context-size"&gt;Check Build Context Size&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;docker build . 2&amp;gt;&amp;amp;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; | head -5
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# &amp;#34;sending build context to Docker daemon 2.5GB&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Fix: reduce context or use .dockerignore&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="use-cache-mounts-correctly"&gt;Use Cache Mounts Correctly&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-dockerfile" data-lang="dockerfile"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# syntax=docker/dockerfile:1.4&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;node:20-alpine&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;RUN&lt;/span&gt; --mount&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;type&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;cache,target&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;/root/.npm &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; npm install&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="run-build-with-debug-output"&gt;Run Build with Debug Output&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;docker build --progress&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;plain -t my-app .
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Example 1: Large build context&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;docker build .
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# error: failed to solve: failed to read dockerfile: ...&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# sending build context 4.2GB&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Fix: create .dockerignore excluding node_modules, .git&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Example 2: Network timeout&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;docker build .
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# error: failed to solve: node:20: failed to resolve&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Fix: check network, use --network=host or retry&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Example 3: Invalid syntax&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;docker build .
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# error: Dockerfile parse error line 15: Unknown instruction: RUN-AND&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Fix: check Dockerfile syntax, ensure proper spacing&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/docker/docker-copy-error/"&gt;Docker COPY Error&lt;/a&gt; — file not found in build context&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/docker/docker-build-cache/"&gt;Docker Build Cache Error&lt;/a&gt; — cache corruption&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/docker/docker-multi-stage/"&gt;Docker Multi-Stage Error&lt;/a&gt; — stage not found&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Docker BuildKit Build Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/docker/docker-buildkit-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/docker/docker-buildkit-error/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A BuildKit build error occurs when the Docker BuildKit engine fails to solve the build graph. BuildKit is the modern build backend for Docker that provides parallel builds and advanced caching, but it can fail when the Dockerfile has issues or the build context is problematic.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build context is too large or contains unnecessary files&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cache mount issues with package managers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Network failure during a build step requiring remote resources&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Invalid Dockerfile syntax not caught by the legacy builder&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Missing or corrupted BuildKit cache&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Platform mismatch in multi-architecture builds&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="enable-buildkit"&gt;Enable BuildKit&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;export DOCKER_BUILDKIT&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Or in /etc/docker/daemon.json:&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# { &amp;#34;features&amp;#34;: { &amp;#34;buildkit&amp;#34;: true } }&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="add-a-dockerignore-file"&gt;Add a .dockerignore File&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-text" data-lang="text"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;node_modules
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;.git
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;*.md
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;.env
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;docker-compose*.yml
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="check-build-context-size"&gt;Check Build Context Size&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;docker build . 2&amp;gt;&amp;amp;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; | head -5
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# &amp;#34;sending build context to Docker daemon 2.5GB&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="use-cache-mounts-correctly"&gt;Use Cache Mounts Correctly&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-dockerfile" data-lang="dockerfile"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# syntax=docker/dockerfile:1.4&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;node:20-alpine&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;RUN&lt;/span&gt; --mount&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;type&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;cache,target&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;/root/.npm &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;\
